## DNS Component Reference

| Component | Lives Where | Job | Logs To |
|---|---|---|---|
| Windows DNS Server | On-premises domain controller | Resolves internal names for domain-joined devices. Forwards unknown public names upstream | `DnsEvents` (only if AMA agent installed) |
| Azure Firewall DNS Proxy | Azure — edge of the VNet | Intercepts all outbound DNS queries from Azure resources. Logs everything, forwards upstream | `AzureDiagnostics` (Category: AzureFirewallDnsProxy) |
| Azure Private DNS Resolver | Azure — inside the VNet | Resolves internal Azure private names and bridges hybrid on-prem to Azure name resolution | `DNSQueryLogs` |
| Public DNS (8.8.8.8 etc.) | Internet — Google, Cloudflare, ISP | Answers public internet name queries. Has no idea about internal company names | Nothing — not in your environment |

